The ANC policy conference is set to take place at the Nasrec Expo Centre between June 30 and July 5, the ANC said in a statement today.The conference is expected to set the tone leading to the elective.The policy conference is held once every five years, and precedes the elective conference. Its purpose, according to the statement, is to develop and review policies aimed at advancing the needs of the country.This year s conference coincides with the African Union meeting scheduled to begin during the first week of July at the AU s headquarters in Addis Ababa.The statement said it was not clear if President Zuma would attend the summit or would delegate this to Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa or International Relations Minister Maite Nkoane Mashabane.-TNA Reporter